channel.title: INtech
channel.description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from INtech, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Samsung S90F QD-OLED TV Review: Refined From Any Angle
item.description: With impeccable accuracy and poise, Samsung’s midrange OLED dazzles on the little things.

item.title: Last 24 hours to grab your +1 pass at 50% off to TechCrunch Disrupt 2026
item.description: Today is the last day to lock in a +1 pass at 50% off to TechCrunch Disrupt 2026, happening on October 13-15 in San Francisco. Register here.

item.title: 6 Best Beard Trimmers (2026): Full Beards, Hair, Stubble
item.description: WIRED has been testing beard trimmers for six years. Our favorite is compact, reliable, ridiculously adjustable, and offers a five-year warranty.

item.title: 'Infinite Jest' Is Back. Maybe Litbros Should Be, Too
item.description: The notoriously challenging book is being re-released for its 30th anniversary. Its fandom is annoying, sure—but at least they read.

item.title: After Minneapolis, Tech CEOs Are Struggling to Stay Silent
item.description: Silicon Valley’s power brokers spent the past year currying favor with President Trump. Two deadly shootings in Minneapolis are now exposing the price...

item.title: The Best Soundbars We’ve Tested: Sonos, Sony, Bose, and More
item.description: Every television deserves a row of speakers to call its own. These are our favorite soundbars from Samsung, Yamaha, Bose, and more.

item.title: How Sequoia-backed Ethos reached the public market while rivals fell short
item.description: The profitable life-insurance platform was one of the first major tech companies to test the 2026 public markets.

item.title: Elon Musk’s SpaceX, Tesla, and xAI in talks to merge, according to reports
item.description: This merger would bring the Grok chatbot, Starlink satellites, and SpaceX rockets together under one corporation.

item.title: The iPhone just had its best quarter ever
item.description: Growth in regions like China and India are credited with pushing Apple's phone sales higher than ever.

item.title: Guys, I don’t think Tim Cook knows how to monetize AI
item.description: One intrepid Morgan Stanley analyst dared to ask how Apple will make money on its AI investments. The answer will not shock you.
